{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_parsifal_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280607757/1957092901/0976.xml":{"full_text":"A-4\nthe SUNDAY STAR, Washington, D. C.\nspun at, asTTUMBia m. mat\nI ~A/mI\n.JPB\nk I|S\nWfekt.\n-mKI^\nawBF\nM Ji\nSH\nJSf js&ddt\nIp y \u25a0*^\u25a0l\"\nSLIGHT ADJUSTMENT\u2014 President Elsenhower at\nthe golf course at Newport, R. 1., yesterday after\nhe sent Senator Russell, Democrat of Georgia, a\nreply to a telegram accusing the President of using\n\u201cpolice state\" methods In Little Rock.\u2014AP Wire\nphoto.\nEisenhower Lays Blame\nFor Riots on Faubus\nContinued From First Page\nator against what he called;\n\"high-handed and illegal meth\nods\u201d being used by the para\ntroopers in Little Rock.\nBut the bitter Elsenhower\nwords seemed aimed primarily\nat Gov. Faubus. without men\ntioning the Governor by name.\nIn Washington. Senator\nRussell said he had received\nMr. Eisenhower's message but\nwould have no comment un\ntil he receives from the Army\nits report on investigation of\nIncidents involving Federal\ntroops at Little Rock.\nSenator Russell said he\nhad asked this data in iden- j\ntical telegrams to the Pres\nident and Secretary of De\nfense Wilson, and that Mr.\nWilson had promised him\nthat the Army would forward\na report on \"alleged wrong\ndoings on the part of soldiers\nat Little Rock.\" The Army\nsaid it will be several days\nbefore it can furnish a re\nport to Senator Russell.\nIn a sense, the President used\nhis telegram to Senator Russell\nto reply to Gov. Faubus' Thurs\nday night television speech\ncalling the use of Federal troops\n\"ill-advised and unwarranted.\"\n\u201cScapegoat.\u201d Faubus Says\nWhen Gov. Faubus heard\nabout it in Little Rock today,\nhe rejoined that \"anybody in\ndifficulty likes to have a scape\nMrs. Eisenhower Recovery\nNot Impeded, Hagerty Says\nBy n star SMS Correspondent\nNEWPORT, R. 1., Sept. 28\nWhite House Press Secretary\nJames C. Hagerty said today\n\u201cthere\u2019s nothing to\" a report\nthat Mrs. Mamie Eisenhower's\nrecovery from a recent opera\ntion has been retarded because\nof a bad reaction to the anes\nthesia she received.\nAsked if her recovery had\nbeen Impeded by anything. Mr.\nHagerty said \"not that I know\nof.\u201d\nMrs. Eisenhower underwent\na gynecological operation at\nWalter Reed Army Hospital in\nWashington several weeks ago.\nII is for INSURANCE\nSave and earn with utmost safety\nand convenience. At Jefferson Federal\nSavings your savings are insured\nup to $10,000; and it\u2019s easy as A-B-C\nfor your money to earn liberal\ndividends. We\u2019re conveniently located\nin our handsome enlarged building\nat the Commercial Crossroads\nof the Capital.\nJefferson Federal Savings\nLoan Association\nFRED A SMITH, PRESIDENT\n17th K STS., N. W EXecutiv* 3-0747\nAssets: Twenty-Five Million Dollars\ngoat\u201d\u2014implying that the Pres\nident is trying to make him the\nscapegoat in the situation.\nThe President told Senator\nRussell he could not under\nstand his comparison of the\nAmerican soldiers in Little\nRock to Hitler's storm troop\ners.\nSenator Russell had charged\nthat, it news reports he cited\nwere true, the soldiers were\n.\u201capplying tactics which must\nhave been copied from the\nmanual issued the officers of\nHitler\u2019s storm troopers.\u201d He\nreferred to reports of one man\nhaving \u201chis head cracked by a\nrifle butt,\u201d and of some other\ncitizens being \u201cpushed down a\nstreet with bayonets at their\nthroats.\u201d\nDoesn\u2019t Challenge Authority\nSenator Russell\u2019s telegram to\nthe President Thursday night\ndid not directly challenge his\nrights to use troops to enforce\ncourt-ordered school integra\ntion, but asserted that \"it has\nnever been contemplated that\nsuch a great aggregation of\nmilitary might would be di\nverted for this purpose.\u2019\u2019\u2019\nMr. Eisenhower's reply was\nmade public at his vacation\nheadquarters on the Newport\nNaval Base today as he pre\npared to wind up his vacation\nMonday or Tuesday.\n\u201cI think I will go home Mon\nday afternoon\u2014it depends on\nwhat Mrs. Ike wants to do,\u201d the\nPresident told Newport Country\nClub Pro Norman Palmer as\nShe appeared to be fully re\ncovered when she came here\nSeptember 4 with the President\nfor a vacation on the Newport\nNaval Base.\nWhile here, Mrs. Eisenhower\nhas stayed most of the time in\nher quarters on the base. She\nhas spent part of the Ume\nworking on plana for the visit\nto the White House next month\nof British Queen Elizabeth and\nPrince Philip.\nMr. Hagerty said there was\nno medical reason for Mrs.\ni Eisenhower not having been\nmore active while in this area.\nthey finished a golf game\nshortly after noon.\nFrees Secretary James C.\nHagerty later said the Presi\ndent definitely would end his\nvacation here either Monday\nafternoon or Tuesday morning.\nHe has been here since Sep\ntember 4, except for three\n\u201ccommuting\u201d trips to Washing\nton.\nWill Meet Governors\nMr. Eisenhower has a sched\nuled conference with a com\nmittee of five Southern Gover\nnors on integration problems\nat the White House in Wash\nington for Tuesday afternoon\nThe Governors asked for the\nmeeting to seek withdrawal of\nFederal troops from Little Rock\n\u201cat the earliest possible mo\nment.\u201d While insisting their\nfunction as a committee of\nthe Southern Governors Con\nference was limited to that,\nthey agred that as individual\nGovernors they could talk\nabout the broader problems Mr.\nElsenhower has in mind.\nWon\u2019t Meet Faubus\nGovernors of Florida. North\nCarolina, Maryland, Tennes\nsee and Georgia make up the\ncommittee.\nThe President ruled out a\nsuggestion that Gov. Faubus\nalso attend. Apparently he\nfeels that the Arkansas Gov\nernor let him down after a\npersonal conference here two\nweeks ago today. He said then\nhe was sure Gov. Faubus de\nsired to use the influence of\nhis office for \u201corderly prog\nress\u201d of court-ordered school\nintegration plans.\nThe difference two weeks can\nmake was evident in Mr. Elsen\nhower\u2019s indirect blast at Gov.\nFaubus in his telegram to Sen\nator Russell. Text of the tele\ngram follows:\n\u201cFew times in my life have\nI felt as saddened as when\nthe obligations of my office re\nquired me to order the use of\nforce within a State to carry\nout the decisions of a Federal\nCourt.\n\"My conviction is that had\nthe police powers of the State\nof Arkansas been utilized not\nto frustrate the orders of the\ncourt but to support them, the\nensuing violence and open dis\nrespect for the law and for\nthe Federal judiciary would\nnever have occurred.\n\u201cThe Arkansas National\nGuard could have handled the\nWalter Erich Jewelers\n1007 Connecticut Am.\nTh. Star* Will In\nClosed All Day Monday,\nSaptnmber 30, 1957\nIn Mwmory of tho Patting of\nEl.soboH. Woltnr\nHUMIDIFIERS\nFit on Any Furnace!\nDo Away With:\nIrritated Ness sad Threat\nChildrea's Colds\nCracking Plaster\nFaraltara Leese at Jeiett\nStatic Electricity\na Sgaaakiag Heart\nInstoll a Humidifier and\nlive more comfortably!\nFrom\n*29\nINSTALLED\n627 F St. N.W.\nST. 3-5500\niltuation with ease had It been\nkutrueted to do ao.\n\u201cAs a matter of fact, had the\nIntegration of Central High\nSchool been permitted to take\nplace without the Intervention\nof the National Guard there\nis little doubt that the process\nwould have gone along quite as\nsmoothly and quietly as it has\nIn other Arkansas communities.\nRequired to Act\n\u201cWhan a State, by seeking\nto frustrate the orders of a\nFederal court, encourages mobs\nof extremists to flout the orders\nof a Federal court, and when\na State refuses to utilize its\npolice powers to protect against\nmobs, persons who are peace\nably exercising their right\nunder the Constitution as de\nfined in such court orders, the\noath of office of the President\nrequires that he take action to\ngive that protection.\n\u201cFailure to act in such a\ncase would be tantamount to\nacquieaence In anarchy and\nthe dissolution of the Union.\n\u201cI must say that I completely\nfail to comprehend your com\nparison of our troops to Hit\nler\u2019s Storm Troopers. In one\ncase military power was used\nto further the ambitious pur\nposes of a ruthless dictator; in\nthe other to preserve the insti\ntutions of free government.\n\u201cYou alleged certain' wrong\ndoings on the part of Individual\ni i\n\nThe AMtWH\nfidelity value P M\nthat startled the\ntrade\nits preview\n.extended range\nHIGH FIDELITY CONSOLETTE\nL w otts ii j. output 4 r\n1\nM m bs. I\u2014 wpfj*\nGIANT 19\" \\I in 1 Pr? S f!\nWOOFER SPEAKER\npY^fwKTER\nO H w Magnificent conioletta styling\nf H Vfi in your choice of groined mo-\nPIPHRPH H |R9 b ond oak or cherry Wl\nsjjfj.,. XjjV colors. a\n7 TRANSISTOR SHORTWAVE I A LA A wmm\nI POCKET RADIO TRA NIC I COB RA\" M A TIC\nPlays where others fail! Not g\njust 4or 5 but 7 transistors q Powered to tune In the world! H _ _ mma k. m _\nlor more sensitivity, more vol- Trons-world short wove eir- H R V. HAKI4W FiC\nume, tone quality that will euits for international recep- H Vd I \u25a0F^ITWbIX\namaze you. Ebony, white, tion plus long distance stand- H\nmoroon, beige or pink; model ord AM broadcast. Marine H 1,4. Aufomoticolly plays 33 Vi, 45, 78\nNo. 500. ond weother coverage \"Block H#. j V|r Qnc j new |g^ 3 rpn-, records!\nSfog\" or genuine cowhide H I 1 0\" t 12\u201c d\nI I plus COBRA-TONE ARM\ne\nI 2-SPEAKER AUTOMATIC I ree P\u00b0 r^,r >9 around the store\nIMk color A\nreceptions, dual speaker Muted yellow, cordovan, dusty I fTill mI Ml II WASHINGTONS LARGEST I\nsound system. Model No. p n afe ora y maroon, j| DISCOUNT ST^^^\nI OPEN FRI. 10 A.M.-9 P.M. OPEN SAT. TIL 6 I Shop Weekdays, 10 A.M. to 9 P.M.\nNegro Legislator\nAsks Pledge of\nWider Trooo Use\nMr the Associated Prsas\nRepresentative Dlrks. Demo\ncrat of Michigan, yesterday\nasked President Eisenhower to\ndeclare that he will use troops\nelsewhere In the South If neces\nsary, as he did in the Little\nRock integration crisis.\nThe Negro lawmaker. In a\nletter to the President, did not\nrefer specifically to the use of\ntroops. But his meaning was\nunmistakable when he said that\nafter the meeting scheduled\nnext Tuesday with five South\nern Governors the President\nshould \u201cmake It perfectly clear\nto the American people through\nthe various media of communi\ncation that you are committed\nto a firm course of action to\nenforce the legal mandates of\nthe Federal judiciary so that\nthere will be no doubt that you\nwill continue the precedent you\nset In the Arkansas case if and\nwhen similar situations occur\nsoldiers at Little Rock. The\nSecretary of the Army will\nassemble the facts and report\nthem directly to you.\n\u201cWith warm regards.\nDwight D. Elsenhower.\"\nrelative to the same issue In\nother Southern areas.\u201d\nMr. Diggs wrote he is hopeful\nthat the conference will per\nsuade the Governors and those\nthey represent \u201cto see the In\nevitably of school desegrega\ntion\u201d and the responsibility for\ncomplying with the law regard\nless of personal feelings.\nBrawl Develops\nIn New Jersey\nCAMDEN, N. J., Sept. 28 m.\n\u2014Five Negro youths entered a\nCamden luncheonette Friday\nnight and battled three white\nboys who were customers at\nthe store, police said. There\nwere no injuries.\nPolice quoted Mrs. Mable\nRyan, 37, co-owner of the\nstore, as saying two Negro boys\nentered the store and knocked\n19-year-old Tony Barbetta.\nCamden, off a stool.\nYoung Barbetta fought back,\nbut three other Negro youths\narmed with sticks entered the\nstore and joined the fight.\nThat brought two white boys,\nBobby Gardner. 19. and John\nHarrington, both of Camden,\nto the Barbetta boy\u2019s aid.\nChairs and tables were upset\nand a plate glass window was\nshattered by,a brick.\nThe Negroes ran off as po\nlice arrived. No reason was\ngiven for the start of the fight.\nAUTOMATIC\nHEATING\ntftyuter, JEKS.\nGAS AND OIL FURNACES\nCompletely Auto